yingyinNormal.en: Chinese New Year is the most important festival in Chinese culture. It is a festival that requires the whole family to get together, so it gives us a concept of reunion.
yingyinNormal.zh: 中国新年在中国文化中是个最重要的节日。这是个全家必须团聚的节日，是个重聚的日子。

yingyinNormal.en: The festival continues the next day with the main event, perhaps the most epic water fight on earth.
yingyinNormal.zh: 节日第二天进入主题，或许这是世界上最声势浩大的水仗。

yingyinNormal.en: This is a new festival but based on a seventeen century tradition when fishermen carved lanterns from ice.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是一个基于十七世纪传统的崭新节日，那时渔民曾用冰块雕刻灯笼。

yingyinNormal.en: You're right, he's a festival of humdrum chitchat.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你说得对，他果然在进行无聊的饭前寒暄。

yingyinNormal.en: We tour Cambulac in preparation for the Festival of the White Moon.
yingyinNormal.zh: 为庆贺白节，我们将巡游大都。

yingyinNormal.en: No, because we don't celebrate the ancient pagan festival of Saturnalia.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不，我们不庆祝古老的异教农神节。

yingyinNormal.en: All I said was that I want to go to the festival. Play for a little while only.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不过就说了句我想去过节，我只想玩一小会儿。

yingyinNormal.en: So, I could take you to a Shakespeare festival. It's happening today and tomorrow.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我可以带你去一个莎士比亚庆典，就是今明两天。

yingyinNormal.en: You should go to that music festival thing with Haley. Do something fun. Learn to relax a...
yingyinNormal.zh: 你应该跟海莉一起去那个音乐节，找点乐子，学会放松…

yingyinNormal.en: Or, a guerilla art exhibit in dumbo? Or, hey, isn't the New York film festival still going on?
yingyinNormal.zh: 或者是一场边缘艺术展？还是？对了，纽约电影节还没结束吧？

yingyinNormal.en: I can't bring Alex to the festival because I am going for work to research new fashion trends.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不能带艾丽克斯去音乐节，因为我是去工作，勘查最新流行趋势。

yingyinNormal.en: "Zayeed Shaheed is a guilty Muslim terrorist who bombed the Milwaukee Festival. Chubbysocks52."
yingyinNormal.zh: 扎耶德·沙希德是穆斯林恐怖分子，他在密尔沃基节引爆了炸弹 「肥袜52」。

yingyinNormal.en: Do we have enough to go to the festival? You're not smart. You never were. Mother and Father said so.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这些钱够我们去过节吗？你一点也不聪明，你一直都这样，父亲和母亲就这么说。

yingyinNormal.en: That was a lovely toast. Kudos. Thank you. Simultaneously, a festival of cloying cliche. You sicken me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 敬酒词说的不错呀，口头表扬一次。谢谢。与此同时，你的敬酒词也老套得让人反胃，你恶心死我了。

yingyinNormal.en: You wanna wander in the hall? Ooh, hey Ben, what if the Holiday Armadillo told you all about the festival of lights?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你想在走廊晃荡吗？班，佳节犰狳跟你说光之节的故事好吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Which do you think she'd prefer? Because I checked the Sheep and Wool Festival Web site, and there's only 8,000 tickets left.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们觉得她最喜欢哪一个？因为我查过羊及羊毛节的官网，只剩8千张票了。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, Amy enjoys knitting her own sweaters, so I was thinking of getting her an all-expense-paid trip to the Wisconsin Sheep and Wool Festival.
yingyinNormal.zh: 艾米喜欢自己织毛衣，我在想自掏腰包赞助她去参加威斯康辛州羊及羊毛节。

yingyinNormal.en: Over the next week, artists will race to transform this plentiful local resource into a giant frozen wonderland, the Harbin ice and snow festival.
yingyinNormal.zh: 整个下一周，艺术家将竞相把这丰富的本地资源转化为巨大无匹的冰雪仙境：哈尔滨冰雪节。

yingyinNormal.en: But this icy river isn't just for extreme sports. All the building materials for the festival at Harbin are taken from this spot to create the city of ice.
yingyinNormal.zh: 除了极限运动外，这条冰河还有其它用处，哈尔滨冰雪节的所有建筑材料都从这里取用，冰城由此而来。
